> <OLD>
>
> Tucson slowly backs away, remaining low to the ground.  He was not about to
> give his position away just yet.  But he wished he could get to the bottom
> of what was going on.  It disturbed him to think he could have lost Rodimus
> for the second time in a row.  But for now he had to hold his position.

<NEW>

Getting to the bottom of things, yes that would be what TUSCON or any
leader would be looking to do. Maximals are missing in fact one of the
leaders is missing, missing with a componant of the Matrix still
beating in his chest. Where was he? Was he truely turned back into a
dark version of himself or was this some clone?

Also Cheetor was still missing as well as well as Optimus Primal?
Where they also being held somewhere in this jungle or where they
elsewhere still waiting for TUSCON to find them? Had anyone even seen
RHINOX in some time? Where had they all gone?

Also, why were the Dinobots attacking Maximals? These were once heros,
ones that centuries ago TUSCON may have called friends! Yes the
Dinobots had not been soon after the Decepticons had surrendered to
the Autobots more than three centuries ago, but what could have
happened to them since? Where they under the control of another or
just out of control?

So many questions and so few answers. This was something would take
time to unravel, if only TUSCON could conquer his own anger and
impatience.

In the distance TUSCON could hear GRIMLOCK and his men in conflict
with something, but mostly what he could hear was their roars of anger
and frustration. There might have been the sound of an engine revving
or was it some sort of explosion? At this range it was difficult to
tell.

Then TUSCON could hear footsteps of something approaching, perhaps two
or three individuals moving through the brush. Where they friend or
enemy? With no IFF signatures there was no way to know. But they were
moving in TUSCON's direction.

(TAG)

Preston
